its 9:26 am my muscles ache i have been sleeping on couches and floors my brain aches i havent been sleeping much at all my heart aches i cant choose to only love one maybe i am aching because i am adjusting. i am goung to curl back onto my brothers couch and aid to my flesh. let it adjust and rest.

-like clothes and jewelry and shoes
 and accessories and mirrors
 creating desires where they should not exist.
 within others, and more so within myself.


maybe what im doing is wrong but
i feel just like that silly lilly allen song

" i dont know whats right and whats real anymore
and i dont know know how im meant to feel anymore"

im so consumed with all of these things.
filling a void, maybe.

im in an old place.
a familiar place, thats not so familiar. the walls are painted, and some are missing, theres new furniture too.
that doesnt change what has happened here. i remember everything. every single detail embedded in these floors,
and these windows, and the roof, mattresses, bathrooms, basements, garage. the road still leads to the lake, and
trails to those old houses, the old pub and the churchyard tombstones, the dog burried in the yard. i could go on endlessly.
this was one of my home away from homes over the past 6 years. i learned so much about myself within these walls.
i miss so much, and i never knew i would.
a rotting house in grand old green township.
holds so many things for our little group. we gathered here tonight and forgot about the wrongs we've done eachother
and just tried to relive a bit of what we loved so dearly, hold onto a few of those strings to our past. those things that
we shared are why we are who we are, why were all still here... as friends. time passed, we aged and learned rough
lessons, and we are still learning.
this is love.
these girls i grew up with. scattered across the house drunken & asleep. we destroyed our youth together, and we
laughed  and cried the whole way through.
i hope we can look back and still lovee every second of it.


this is rambling and possibly senseless. but its real.
i had something to say... but i think i lost it in this glass of cheap vodka and blue mountain dew.

i have had this obsession that is dissolving my soul.
its so beautiful... i just ... i cannot begin to describe it.
for it will do no justice.

have a listen for yourself

i haven't been alone for several months.
i cant even recognize how peaceful it is. that i need it. that everyone needs time alone to think and breathe.
 or just be. and do nothing.
but i have fallen so in love and become so devastatingly attached, that several moments after we part the other night,
 i grew anxious and delirious. my mood spell was so severe it developed into a panic attack.
all through the night i was tossing and turning, trying to think myself asleep.
my phone rang.
my love was on the other end
- dealing with the same symptoms.

is that dangerous?
it has to be. going through withdrawl from someone?
needing them so bad that you can not even function properly without them.
i mean, what would come of either of us if something awful were to happen?

i couldn't possibly bear it.
i do not even want to conjure up such thoughts.
for i will become physically sick

love sweet love

to disregard things.
and maybe thats bad, but ic ant take eevrything to heart, and i sure as hell cant keep analyzing things the way i do.

Denis told me just to take a step back and let things happen for a little while, stop trying to figure everything out and just enjoy it before its gone.
he is right. so i am trying so hard. but when the hurt resurects its painful and icky and i lose control.
but i am working on it.
i dont want to not care but i feel like i am masking my real emotions, thus being fake and such.
i cant do that.
i am lost.
but finding a way.


true love is neevr easy i suppose.
and i like the challenge.

im IN love!

its something awful that it took me until senior year to see true colors come from beneath 
the concealing layer of make-up and flesh of the people i believed to be my "friends"

i have a small handfull of people that i trust and adore.
the others have betrayed me in unspeakable manners, 
but those who have not are on pedestals.

i am ever so grateful for the ones i have left.
for they exceed anything i could ever dream for.

that much more.
everything is so perfect.

i will just play pretend, thats all you are doing anyway.
but i bite my tongue and force a smile. cause i love so deep, i know nothing else but to cope.

the snow has already found means to seep into my flesh, even though it refuses to stick to the grass, and the trees, and other select things. my eyelashes being an exception. which lit me up when i saw them just resting on the black little strings that seel my eyelids when i got into the car. the heat melted them away. into my pores. i adore that feeling, this winter feeling. everything falls into place, and dissolves. so destructive and beautiful. simualtaneously.
i am peeling back layers. so i can play that familiar game, of  finding the unfamiliar.
